put the boot in
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to kick a prostrate foe, to kick (when down).
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:-
Notes: ca1951 R. Barraclough (Wellington) `especially in a fight, to use ungentlemanly tactics'.
Citations
